La Honda first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2010 U.S. census]].<ref name=2010CensusCA/>

The [[2020 United States census]] reported that La Honda had a population of 979. The population density was {{convert|230.0|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of La Honda was 789 (80.6%) [[White Americans|White]], 3 (0.3%) [[African Americans|African American]], 3 (0.3%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 28 (2.9%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 2 (0.2%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 46 (4.7%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 108 (11.0%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 148 persons (15.1%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=La Honda CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0639318 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 23, 2025}}</ref>

There were 420 households, out of which 97 (23.1%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 213 (50.7%) were married-couple households, 38 (9.0%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 73 (17.4%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 96 (22.9%) had a male householder with no partner present. 104 households (24.8%) were one person, and 55 (13.1%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.33.<ref name=DP1/> There were 265 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (63.1% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=La Honda CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0639318 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 23, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 142 people (14.5%) under the age of 18, 34 people (3.5%) aged 18 to 24, 259 people (26.5%) aged 25 to 44, 317 people (32.4%) aged 45 to 64, and 227 people (23.2%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 48.9{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 120.0 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 457 housing units at an average density of {{convert|107.4|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 420 (91.9%) were occupied. Of these, 256 (61.0%) were owner-occupied, and 164 (39.0%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

